# Spring Error Code Template

## Generation Goal
- Generate consistent backend error handling artifacts:
  - centralized `ErrorCode` enum/registry
  - `ApiResponse` error contract helper
  - `GlobalExceptionHandler` exception-to-code mapping

## Required Artifacts
- `common/exception/ErrorCode.java`
- `common/response/ApiResponse.java` (or update existing wrapper)
- `common/exception/GlobalExceptionHandler.java`
- custom exceptions:
  - `ResourceNotFoundException`
  - `BusinessException`
  - `ValidationException`

## ErrorCode Enum Template
- Each enum entry must include:
  - machine code (`CATEGORY_XXXX`)
  - default human message
- Example:

```java
public enum ErrorCode {
    USER_NOT_FOUND("USER_0001", "User not found"),
    INVALID_EMAIL("USER_0002", "Invalid email"),
    INVALID_TOKEN("AUTH_0001", "Invalid authentication token"),
    SYSTEM_ERROR("SYSTEM_9999", "Unexpected system error");

    private final String code;
    private final String message;

    ErrorCode(String code, String message) {
        this.code = code;
        this.message = message;
    }

    public String code() { return code; }
    public String message() { return message; }
}
```

## ApiResponse Error Template
- Error response shape must include:
  - `success: false`
  - `error_code`
  - `message`
  - optional `details`
- Example factory:

```java
public static <T> ApiResponse<T> error(ErrorCode errorCode) {
    return new ApiResponse<>(false, null, errorCode.code(), errorCode.message(), null);
}
```

## GlobalExceptionHandler Template
- Use `@RestControllerAdvice` and map exception classes to `ErrorCode`.
- Minimum mappings:
  - `ResourceNotFoundException` -> `404`
  - validation exceptions -> `400`
  - auth exceptions -> `401/403`
  - fallback -> `SYSTEM_9999` with `500`
- Example logging format:

```java
log.error("error_code={} request_id={} user_id={} message={}",
    errorCode.code(), requestId, userId, ex.getMessage(), ex);
```

## Template Safety Rules
- Never return raw stack trace to client.
- Never return error without `error_code`.
- Never modify existing released error codes.
- Add new error scenario by adding a new unique code only.
